{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place teabags in a large bowl then place bowl on mixing bowl lid. Weigh in boiling water and allow to steep for 5 minutes.","Add dried fruit then remove bowl from lid and gently mix together. Cover with cling film and set aside to steep for 8 hours or overnight.","The next day, preheat oven to 150°C and line a large loaf tin (900 g) with baking paper.","Place sugar, flour, mixed spice and egg in mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Remove and discard teabags from soaked fruits. Add fruits and juices then mix <b>15 sec\/\/speed 4<b> while stirring with spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid. Finish mixing with spatula before pouring into prepared loaf tin. Bake for 1¼-1½ hours (150°C) or until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean.","Leave in tin for 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely. Once cool, cut in slices and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 teabags (e.g. Earl Grey or English Breakfast)","300 g water, boiling","450 g dried mixed fruit","250 g light brown sugar","450 g self-raising flour","2 tsp mixed spice","1 large egg"]}],"id":"r82890","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-50Wtp63miug\/XZWqgLOrewI\/AAAAAAAAfY0\/yjZnfJLI8p4vp83_k4jWwrbW4Yk5ry7PQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_NC03YAgSArlLxHks.png","title":"Bara Brith","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.9 g","fat":"1.2 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"76.1 g","calories":"1399 kJ \/ 334 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, baking paper, 900 g loaf tin (2 lb), skewer, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This traditional Welsh tea bread, which translates literally as ‘speckled bread’, has several variations. It can be made with yeast, but this is a quicker version without. The tea-soaked fruits give the loaf a lovely sticky texture and it keeps well, too. Best enjoyed cut in thick slices and spread with butter."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","10h","12 slices"]}